text:
I encountered some problems using trying to use the import task outside of the
normal Ant execution environment (I'm using Groovy ant scripting).
I was getting the error - "import only allowed as a top-level task"

Looking at the code that implements this edit:
        if(getOwningTarget() == null || !"".equals(getOwningTarget().getName()))
            throw new BuildException("import only allowed as a top-level task");

This seems invalid to me....
Shouldn't the edit be:

        if(getOwningTarget() != null && !"".equals(getOwningTarget().getName()))
            throw new BuildException("import only allowed as a top-level task");
